== Living beings == {| class="wikitable" |- ! Counter ! Japanese ! Reading ! Examples for 1, 2, ..., 10, |- |People |人 |にん |ひとり、ふたり、さんにん(3)、...、じゅうにん、 |- |(Small) Animals |匹 |ひき |いっぴき、にひき、...、じゅっぴき、 |- |Large animals |頭 |とう |いっとう、にとう、...、じゅっとう、 |- |Birds, rabbits |羽 |わ |いちわ、にわ、...、じゅうわ、 |- |(Small) fish and shrimp |尾 |び |いちび、にび、...、じゅうび、 |} 匹 is often used for animals generally, but in more careful use it is restricted to small animals, such as cats and dogs.
Large animals notably include horses, cattle, elephants, also whales, dolphins.
Some kinds of animals have two or more counters. For example, "3 butteflies" can be translated into 3羽 or 3匹.
